text: Itkulovo () is a rural locality (a village) in Abzanovsky Selsoviet, Zianchurinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 383 as of 2010. There are 6 streets. == Geography == It is located 55 km from Isyangulovo, 6 km from Abzanovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Zianchurinsky District
title: Itkulovo
